<br>
What happens if you should go back in time then eat your grandfather. Well, you would be a cannibal for one thing. There's also the matter of changing the future. If your grandfather doesn't have a son then your father and consequently YOU will never exsist. But hang on a minute. If you never existede then how in the dickens did you build a time machine (or order it through Mad Scientists monthly magazine) then travel back in time with it? You couldn't have. So you couldn't have commited ancestral cannibalism.<br>
<br>
Now if that's the case then your grandfather lived, had ankle biters including you father and you were subsequently born. So you WERE born. Now you build the machine, go back, eat pops, were never born, didn't go back in time, were born.....<br>
<br>
This was how thinking on parallel universes developed. According to special relativity practical time travel into the past is indeed possible. Just not in this universe. You arrive in another. One which may be exactly like the time you wished to visit. Getting back to your own universe might prove impossible.   <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
